proof.block.caption:
			Vector addition is commutative: 
               \mathbf{x} + \mathbf{y} = \mathbf{y} + \mathbf{x}
            , geometric proof

para.para.body:
In our geometric interpretation of vector addition, 
                  \mathbf{x} + \mathbf{y}
                corresponds to an arrow diagram in which 
                  \mathbf{y}
                follows the vector 
                  \mathbf{x}
               . On the other hand, 
                  \mathbf{y} + \mathbf{x}
                corresponds to a vector diagram which 
                  \mathbf{x}
                follows the vector 
                  \mathbf{y}
               .

Both of the vectors 
                              \mathbf{x} + \mathbf{y}
                            and 
                              \mathbf{y} + \mathbf{x}
                            are represented by the same diagonal of the vector addition parallelogram.

