proof.block.caption:
			Addivitive inverse of   
               \mathbf{x}
            : 
               \mathbf{x} + (-1)\cdot \mathbf{x} = \mathbf{0}
            , geometric argument

para.para.body:
Reversing a vector 
                  \mathbf{x}
               , yields the vector 
                  -\mathbf{x}
               , and concatenating 
                  \mathbf{x}
                with its reverse yields the vector which starts and ends at the same point; i.e. the 
                  \mathbf{0}
               -vector. Accordingly, the additive inverse of 
                  \mathbf{x}
                is 
                  -\mathbf{x}
               , as was to be shown.

proof.block.caption:
			Addivitive inverse of 
               \mathbf{x}
            : 
               \mathbf{x} + (-1)\cdot \mathbf{x} = \mathbf{0}
            , algebraic argument

para.para.body:
This confirms that 
                  \mathbf{y}=-\mathbf{x}
                is the additive inverse of 
                  \mathbf{x}
               .

